Princess Aurora of Everglen

Future Ruler | Curse Breaker | Diplomat of Enchanted Realms



Objective

To serve as a beacon of hope, courage, and kindness within the kingdom, while managing magical crises, uniting diverse creatures, and ensuring that all citizens (enchanted or otherwise) live happily ever after.



Experience

Royal Apprentice, Everglen Kingdom Childhood – Present

Represented the royal family at balls, coronations, and public feasts.

Mediated disputes between woodland animals, dwarves, and talking furniture.

Escaped multiple kidnappings and tower imprisonments, demonstrating resilience and crisis management.

Partnered with fairy godmothers, wizards, and princes on kingdom-wide problem solving.

Enchanted Forest Intern Seasonal Quests

Collaborated with magical creatures to maintain forest harmony.

Collected intelligence on witches, curses, and suspicious stepmothers.

Rescued lost villagers with guidance from birds, mice, and enchanted maps.



Skills

Diplomacy and alliance building; fluent in royal etiquette and animal languages (avian, rodent, dragon).

Crisis management, including curse survival, troll negotiations, and spell-breaking.

Public performance: skilled in spontaneous singing and waltzing.

Wardrobe and presentation: able to maintain impeccable gowns in hostile conditions.

Leadership: inspires loyalty in citizens and companions alike.



Education

Royal Academy of Enchanted Studies Major: Grace and Diplomacy Minor: Curse Survival and Songcraft



Honors and Awards

“Fairest in the Land” (peer-reviewed, annually contested).

Recipient of the Happily Ever After Distinction for outstanding service in fairy-tale resolution.



References

Fairy Godmother

Seven Dwarves Union

Talking Mirror (available upon reflection)
